                      <span>2001-09-18</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>This is a great book for those of us who are NOT PKI development engineers. I learned a lot from this book; the authors, Russ Housley and Tim Polk, were able to present technical material in a way that was completely understandable to non-technical people who are interested in Internet and computer security issues. The Appendix on ASN.1, for example, clarified structures for me. As a policy person, I particularly enjoyed the Chapter on PKI Policy, thought it well written, succinct, and right on target. Since I read this book, I have referenced it in presentations and papers on the subject. Great work!</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">A credit to the authors</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
