                    </div>
                    <span>Planning for PKI is without doubt the Class of all books related to PKI. The authors have done a marvelous job of creating a book that walks the fine line of being interesting to senior management as well as Engineers.<P>For the CIO, it provides wonderful examples of how PKI can benefit your organization.<P>For engineers and techies that it provides the nuts and bolts of Public Key Infrastructure, (CP and CPS development, public key encryption ,Architecture, CRLs, Cross Certification, Applications, etc.)<P>It is truely a credit to the authors, and I would recommend it to anyone who has even the smallest bit of interest in PKI.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Very useful guide to PKI.</div>
